# Unit Prefixes

In the International System of Units (SI),
designations of multiples and subdivision of any unit may be arrived at by combining with the name of the unit the prefixes.

Smaller quantities or sub units:

```
>>> (10.deci, 1E1.deci)
(1, 1)

>>> (100.centi, 1E2.centi)
(1, 1)

>>> (1000.milli, 1E3.milli)
(1, 1)

>>> (1000000.micro, 1E6.micro)
(1, 1)

>>> (1000000000.nano, 1E9.nano)
(1, 1)

>>> (1000000000000.pico, 1E12.pico)
(1, 1)
```

Larger quantities or whole units:

```
>>> (0.1.deca, 1E-1.deca)
(1, 1)

>>> (0.01.hecto, 1E-2.hecto)
(1, 1)

>>> (0.001.kilo, 1E-3.kilo)
(1, 1)

>>> (0.000001.mega, 1E-6.mega)
(1, 1)

>>> (0.000000001.giga, 1E-9.giga)
(1, 1)

>>> (0.000000000001.terra, 1E-12.terra)
(1, 1)
```

_Note_:
_terra_ is sometimes spelled _tera_,
_deca_ is sometimes spelled _deka_.

